<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1913-10-28T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1913-10-28T00:00:00-05:00" n="538" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d538">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 422.11G93/696.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Minister of Ecuador</gloss> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">New York</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1913-10-28">
                                    <hi rend="italic">October 28, 1913</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>At our interview of the 14th I assured Mr. Moore that the phrase “juicio
                            final” used in my note of August 8 meant unappealable judgment. I
                            received yesterday from my Government a cablegram that says: <quote rend="blockquote">
                                <p>Congress empowers Executive to accept unappealable award.</p>
                            </quote>
                        </p>
                        <p>Every difficulty being removed, I expect of your excellency’s justice
                            that you will deign to direct that Judge Miller perform the duties of
                            the office he has accepted.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Minister of Ecuador.</hi>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>